										or after your appointment=E2=80=99s end time. Buffer Before:
										Applying a buffer before your service will add some padding
										before the start time. For instance, if your service's
										duration is 1 hour and you have a 15 minute buffer before
										the appointment, then your client who schedules at 9:00 am
										would have you reserved starting at 8:45 am. And the Buffer
										After: Applying a buffer after your service will add some
										time padding after the end time. For example, if your
										service's duration is 1 hour and you have a 15 minute buffer
										after the appointment, then a client who schedules at 9:00
										am would have you reserved until 9:15 am.
									</p>
